devdoc.author: Set Protocol Module that enables SetTokens to perform atomic trades using Decentralized Exchanges such as 1inch or Kyber. Integrations mappings are stored on the IntegrationRegistry contract.

params._setToken: Instance of the SetToken to initialize

trade(address,string,address,uint256,add.details: Although the SetToken units are passed in for the send and receive quantities, the total quantity sent and received is the quantity of SetToken units multiplied by the SetToken totalSupply.

params._data: Arbitrary bytes to be used to construct trade call data
params._exchangeName: Human readable name of the exchange in the integrations registry
params._minReceiveQuantity: Min units of token in SetToken to be received from the exchange
params._receiveToken: Address of the token that will be received from the exchange
params._sendQuantity: Units of token in SetToken sent to the exchange
params._sendToken: Address of the token to be sent to the exchange
params._setToken: Instance of the SetToken to trade
